# HIVE Accessibility & Interaction Standards

## Visual Accessibility
- **Text Contrast**: 4.5:1 minimum
- **UI Elements**: 3:1 minimum contrast
- **Focus Indicators**:
  - #EEB700 ring
  - 2px width minimum
  - Always visible
  - 4px blur for glow effect
- **Color Usage**:
  - Never sole indicator of state
  - Support high contrast mode
  - Clear differentiation for states

## Motion & Animation
- **Duration Standards**:
  - Micro-interactions: 150-250ms
  - Standard transitions: 300-400ms
  - Complex transitions: 500ms maximum
- **Rules**:
  - No decorative animations
  - Maximum 2 concurrent animations
  - Must respect prefers-reduced-motion
  - All motion must have purpose
- **Fallbacks**:
  - Replace animations with haptics
  - Use subtle spatial changes
  - Maintain state clarity

## Multimodal Feedback System
- **Every interaction must provide**:
  - Visual feedback (motion, color, spacing)
  - Haptic feedback (when appropriate)
  - Auditory feedback (optional, off by default)
  - Spatial feedback (transitions, layers)

## Haptic Patterns
- **Touch Feedback**:
  - Tap: Light impact
  - Long press: Medium impact
  - Success: Confirmation pattern
  - Error: Sharp triple + vibrate
- **Rules**:
  - Must respect system settings
  - Consistent across similar actions
  - Never excessive or distracting
  - Support haptic reduction preferences

## Focus Management
- **Visual Indicators**:
  - Always visible
  - High contrast
  - Clear movement
- **Navigation**:
  - Logical tab order
  - No focus traps
  - Skip links for main content
  - Keyboard shortcuts documented
- **Structure**:
  - Semantic heading hierarchy
  - Proper ARIA landmarks
  - Clear section boundaries

## Error Handling
- **Visual Feedback**:
  - Distinct error states
  - Warm red borders
  - Gentle shake animation
  - Inward glow effect
- **Messages**:
  - Specific, not generic
  - Action-oriented guidance
  - Clear recovery steps
  - Proper error codes when relevant
- **Interaction**:
  - Immediate validation feedback
  - Easy error recovery
  - Maintain entered data
  - Keyboard accessible solutions

## Implementation Requirements
- **Structure**:
  - Semantic HTML/Flutter widgets
  - Proper ARIA roles and labels
  - Consistent heading hierarchy
  - Clear component boundaries
- **Testing**:
  - Screen reader compatibility
  - Keyboard navigation
  - Touch target size (44x44pt min)
  - Color contrast verification
- **Support**:
  - Multiple input methods
  - Assistive technologies
  - System preferences
  - Reduced motion/animation

## Ritual UX Requirements
- **Emotional Events**:
  - Must feel alive and responsive
  - Clear state transitions
  - Appropriate feedback intensity
  - Celebratory moments
- **Feedback Layers**:
  - Visual celebration
  - Haptic confirmation
  - Optional sound
  - Spatial awareness